When I was in Kansas
getting Coach with my dad,

00:34:36.800 --> 00:34:39.940
we actually spent a
few hours in the prison

00:34:39.940 --> 00:34:42.139
where our dogs were trained.

00:34:42.139 --> 00:34:44.620
And we walked into the
room, and all the inmates

00:34:44.620 --> 00:34:47.080
were sitting there with the
dogs that they were currently

00:34:47.080 --> 00:34:49.179
training at the
time, and they all

00:34:49.179 --> 00:34:51.300
started tearing up
because they were getting

00:34:51.300 --> 00:34:53.020
so emotional over
seeing these dogs

00:34:53.020 --> 00:34:57.510
and seeing them with the people
that they would be helping.

00:34:57.510 --> 00:35:00.690
And I got to meet one
of the two trainers

00:35:00.690 --> 00:35:03.120
that got to train Coach.

00:35:03.120 --> 00:35:07.007
And I was a little
nervous at first,

00:35:07.007 --> 00:35:08.840
because it was a little
intimidating, 'cause

00:35:08.840 --> 00:35:13.060
he was a very, very large man.

00:35:13.060 --> 00:35:17.780
But he was so sweet,
and got really touched

00:35:17.780 --> 00:35:20.160
that Coach was helping
someone like me

00:35:20.160 --> 00:35:25.620
and that he could be a part
of an organization like CARES.

